---
// Quick "what is Flue" callout for CF-native readers. Three points, no marketing.
---

<section class="why">
  <h2>Why Flue on top of Workers?</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>It's an agent harness, not an SDK.</strong> Same shape as Claude Code or Codex:
      sessions, skills, sandboxes, message history, tool calls — but headless and
      programmable. You write a function, not a chat UI.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Cloudflare is the runtime.</strong> Every agent becomes a Worker. Sessions
      persist in Durable Objects automatically. R2 is the agent's filesystem. No Redis, no
      Postgres, no infra to provision.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Build once, deploy anywhere.</strong> Same Flue agent runs on Workers, Node,
      GitHub Actions, GitLab CI. The examples below all deploy to Workers via{' '}
      <a href="https://alchemy.run">alchemy</a> (no wrangler config), but the agent code is
      portable.
    </li>
  </ul>
</section>

